    Pulling the Full SFO Passengers Dataset

    sfo_data.Rd

    Due to size limitation, the sfo_passengers dataset containes data up to Dec 2020. The get_sfo_passengers functions enables to pull the full dataset directly from the package repository.

    sfo_data(type = "passengers")

    Arguments

    type

    A character, the type of dataset - "passengers" (default) or "stats"

    Value

    A data.frame objects with 12 columns

passengers_agg <- passengers_df %>%
  group_by(date, activity_type_code) %>%
  summarise(total = sum(passenger_count),
            .groups = "drop")

head(passengers_agg)
#> # A tibble: 6 × 3
#>   date       activity_type_code   total
#>   <date>     <chr>                <int>
#> 1 2005-07-01 Deplaned           1627329
#> 2 2005-07-01 Enplaned           1569412
#> 3 2005-07-01 Thru / Transit       29028
#> 4 2005-08-01 Deplaned           1614468
#> 5 2005-08-01 Enplaned           1553146
#> 6 2005-08-01 Thru / Transit       28252

plot_ly(data = passengers_agg |> filter(activity_type_code == "Deplaned"),
        x = ~ date,
        y = ~ total,
        type = "scatter",
        mode = "lines") |>
  layout(title = "Total Air Passengers Landed in SFO",
         yaxis = list(title = "Number of Passengers"),
         xaxis = list(title = "Data source: San Francisco data portal (DataSF)"))
